<br>
He didnt even finish high school? Then im VERY impressed.<br>
<br>
I saw in another thread, i dont remember where it was and i dont mean to quote it but use it as an argument. Someone said that violence have been on earth forever. If we take away guns people would resort to sticks and stones to do their killings. In a way that might be true, altho killing someone with a knife is so much more personal than with a gun. And a kid couldnt take out half of their school with a knife. <br>
<br>
And as one of the school shooting victims father said, why should you be able to keep a fully automatic rifle and submachinegun at home? There is no use for them.<br>
<br>
His ultimate question, why all guns and violence exist at the ratio it does in the states, he cant answer. His theory would be fear. How much water does that statement hold?<br>
