<br>
I agree with you, don't get me wrong.  I was just pointing out that Moore isn't exactly an objective observer.  I'm a gun control advocate, as I said in the other thread.  I don't think that completely outlawing guns is realistic, but I think much stricter standards and requirements should be applied to current and potential gun owners.  There's also no need for civilians to own assault rifles, or semi-automatics that can be easily converted to full auto with a $100 kit from the internet.<br>
<br>
Homer:  &quot;I need to buy a gun.&quot;<br>
Shop Owner:  &quot;Okay sir, just fill out these forms and then come back in 3 days.&quot;<br>
Homer:  &quot;3 days?!&quot;<br>
Shop Owner:  &quot;3 day waiting period before firearm purchase, sir.&quot;<br>
Homer:  &quot;But I'm angry NOW!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
That pretty much sums it up I think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malinkinuikila>Malinki Nuikila</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#628CBC>(2/22/03 2:18:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=446.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bowling for Columbine</span><hr size=1> It's all about growing up.<br>
<br>
Cain killed Abel.  Since then, mankind has become more and more efficient in the process of taking another life.  You either grow up and mature, or you stay an immature child, falling farther and farther behind someone else.  And someone else just might, for whatever reason, want to take advantage of that.<br>
<br>
Yes, people will kill people with whatever they can, if they really want to.  Knives, screwdrivers, clubs, nuclear devices, whatever.  Yes, that's the same old statement, and I do believe it's true.  History supports it.<br>
<br>
But the fact of the matter is as I said above.  People either grow and learn, or they fall behind the rest of society.  In every single aspect, including the taking of a life.<br>
<br>
It's not an issue of fear.  It's an issue of growing up and accepting responsibility.  Facing up to the fact that life just plain sucks sometimes.  Something that I personally feel Michael Moore has yet to face up to.  He's too content to point out supposed lack of responsibility in others.<br>
<br>
Keep up, or fall behind, people.  That's the simple truth here, as distasteful as it may be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=446.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=446.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=446.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/mt/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=446.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=446.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=446.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=446.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub169.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="mtboardsfrm1">General<option value="mtboardsfrm2">Market<option value="mtboardsfrm3">Rants<option value="mtboardsfrm4">Raves and Accomplishments<option value="mtboardsfrm5">Off Topic<option value="mtboardsfrm6">Funnies<option value="mtb